itle, which also employs diagrams to illustrate the text.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Aug 2020) 0aMilitary art and sciencevEarly works to 1800. 0aTacticsvEarly works to 1800. 4aAntike. 4aMilitär. 4aTactics. 4aTaktik. 4aantiquity. 4amilitary. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh1 aAsklepiodotos, , eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aBrodersen, Kai, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2017z978311071954308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2017z9783110540550oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2017z9783110547733oZDB-23-DGD0 cprintz978311056216340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311056559140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110565591423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110565591.jpg  a978-3-11-071954-3  DG Plus eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGDb2017  aZDB-23-DGGb2017